modules.description: Generates s-expressions from a domain-specific language embedded in OCaml code, allowing structured representation of values and context. It processes literals, variables, and formatted strings to build sexp trees directly within expressions. Used to create detailed error logs and debug outputs with minimal boilerplate.

Generates S-expression representations from labeled expressions and expands embedded patterns into explicit match cases. Operates on OCaml AST nodes, including labels, expressions, and locations. Used to transform pattern-matching syntax into verbose, readable S-expressions for serialization or analysis.
